Uses of Package
ca.uqac.lif.cep

  • Packages that use ca.uqac.lif.cep 
    Package Description
    ca.uqac.lif.cep
    Elementary classes defining all the basic concepts of event stream processing.
    ca.uqac.lif.cep.cli
    Rudimentary interactive command-line interpreter and GUI.
    ca.uqac.lif.cep.functions
    Functions and function trees
    ca.uqac.lif.cep.input
    Processors to handle conversions to and from various data formats.
    ca.uqac.lif.cep.interpreter
    Interpreter for queries written in ESQL, the Event Stream Query Language.
    ca.uqac.lif.cep.io
    Processors to handle input and output of data from external sources, such as files and pipes.
    ca.uqac.lif.cep.numbers
    A set of elementary functions for manipulating numbers .
    ca.uqac.lif.cep.tmf
    Processors to manipulate traces of generic events.
    ca.uqac.lif.cep.tuples
    Processors and functions for event traces made of tuples of name-value pairs.
  • Classes in ca.uqac.lif.cep used by ca.uqac.lif.cep 
    Class and Description
    Connector.ConnectorException
    Exception thrown when a problem occurs when connecting two processors
    Context
    Associative map used by processors to store persistent data
    Contextualizable 
    GroupProcessor
    Encapsulates a chain of processors as if it were a single one.
    GroupProcessor.ProcessorAssociation
    Tuple made of a number and a processor.
    Palette
    Provides extensions to the original parser's grammar
    Palette.PaletteEntry
    Represents one of the processors provided by this palette.
    PipeCrawler
    Visits every processor
    Processor
    Receives zero or more input events, and produces zero or more output events.
    ProcessorBox
    Information about the graphical representation of a processor in an editor.
    ProcessorBox.Coordinate
    Representation of a pixel in an image
    ProcessorBox.Coordinate.Orientation
    Orientation of the processor's port in its graphical representation
    ProcessorSettings
    Representation of a set of parameters regulating the instantiation and the operation of a processor.
    ProcessorSettings.Setting
    One of the parameters regulating the operation of some processor
    Pullable
    Queries events on one of a processor's outputs.
    Pullable.NextStatus
    The "next" status of the pullable.
    PullConstant
    Returns the same event over and over when pulled
    Pushable
    Gives events to some of a processor's input.
    SingleProcessor
    Performs a computation on input events to produce output events.
